The mere thought of snakes is enough to send shivers down the spines of most people. Here in the Lowveld snakes form a very big past of our biodiversity and therefore people often encounter them. In reality there is actually little need for worry as only a handful pose a potential threat to humans. By educating yourself you will be able to tell the difference.Click on the images and buttons for more. Also be sure to scroll to the bottom for a printer friendly version of our emergency numbers, first aid procedures, international snake bite statistics and some fun snake facts. &nbsp;Images and text courtesy of Johan Marais, author of A Complete Guide to the Snakes of Southern Africa.Videos courtesy of Daniel Louw, except where stated otherwise.&nbsp;